 a global provider of billing and customer care solutions for voice data video and content services headquartered in yokneam israel the company also has offices in silver spring md in the united states of america iaşi in romania and suceava in romania contents  history  inception ipo and growth history  auction rate securities  mantiloking cdo  and mind cti ltds arbitration claim against credit suisse  suit by sarit tamar against mind cti ltd and certain of the companys directors and officers  suit by mind cti ltd against its accountant kesselmann and kesselmann  share buyback  dividend  products  customers  see also  external links  references historyedit inception ipo and growth historyedit mind cti ltd was founded in  by the companys current chief executive officer monica iancu née eisinger and lior salansky in yokneam israel in august  the company had an initial public offering on nasdaq and in  the company’s shares were also listed on the telaviv stock exchange and were included in the ta index of leading shares for a while but in norvember of  the company delisted from the telaviv stock exchange tase mndo and now is listed exclusive with nasdaq at the time of its initial public offering the company reported revenues of us  million and net income of us million for year  and had raised funding of approximately us million from adc teledata communications ltd a subsidiary of adc telecommunications and a syndicate of investors including summit ventures the initial public offering yielded net proceeds of us million for the company and in  the company reported revenues of us million net income of us million and working capital of us million as of december   in  the company acquired from veramark technologies inc all the rights for the verabill product line a mediation provisioning and billing solution for wireline and wireless midsize carriers for us million in  the company acquired sentori inc a provider of customer care and billing solutions to rural wireless carriers and mvnos mainly in the united states for an estimated us million in cash noting that the transaction carried a goodwill of us million intangible assets of us million and current liabilities of us million in  the company acquired omni consulting company limited doing business as abacus billing a provider of billing and customer care solutions in a service bureau mode mainly in europe for an estimated us million in cash including expenses and performance related earnouts providing for payments through the third quarter of  of up to a maximum of approximately us million noting that the transaction carried goodwill of us million not including goodwill from the performance related earnouts intangible assets of us million and current liabilities of us million from  through  the company encountered difficulties with the investment of a large part of its assets in auction rate securities causing writeoffs of significant investments from  through  however these writeoff were eventually offset through the settlement of an arbitration action against credit suisse group ag aggravating the difficulties with the investments during the  through  timeperiod the company experienced difficulties growing recording no netnew business in  subsequent to the  settlement agreement with credit suisse group ag the company was sued by an individual investor purportedly in a class action securities lawsuit relating primarily to the companys investment in auction rate securities the lawsuit was dismissed in july  in  the company resumed its growth securing new key wins including wins with tier  operators and wins related to the deregulation and emerging mvno market in israel in  the company announced that it would actively pursue acquisitions that satisfied certain criteria including proven revenue generation complementary technology and geography and expected accretion to earnings within two to three quarters as of december   the company had no employees in the united kingdom in february  the company started its second location in romania in the city of suceava auction rate securitiesedit mantiloking cdo  and mind cti ltds arbitration claim against credit suisseedit in the years prior to  mind cti ltd had us million almost twothirds of its then current assets tied up in collateralized debt obligation cdo bond investments issued by merrill lynch and structured as auction rate securities arss which were subsequently written down in their entirety in september  the company recovered us million of the failed investment in an arbitrated settlement with credit suisse group ag its financial adviser and subsequently in december  the company paid out an extraordinary dividend of us per share to its shareholders in its statement of claim filed on february   with the financial industry regulatory authority against credit suisse its investment bank and certain credit suisse employees the company alleged among other things that the bank was supposed to invest the companys funds in highly liquid highly safe day auction rate securities but  without the companys authorization  invested the funds  in a security called mantoloking arss and sought recovery of us million the arbitration action was related to united states vs butler an indictment of two credit suisse bankers julian tzolov and eric butler for among other things securities and wire fraud alleging that tzolov and butler represented investments in cdoarss as low risk products guaranteed by the united states government and concealed or falsified the names of the investments to make it appear that these products were other types of arss than cdoarss by removing the term cdo from the name of the investment adding the term student loan or sl or doing both tzolov pleaded guilty to in july  and butler was convicted in august  as part of the arbitration settlement the company was also reimbursed for us million of its legal costs related to the arbitration suit by sarit tamar against mind cti ltd and certain of the companys directors and officersedit during  sarit tamar an individual shareholder in the company filed a purported class action securities lawsuit against the company certain of the companys officers and one of the companys directors the complaint sought unspecified compensatory damages for among other things alleged misleading statements relating primarily to the companys investment in auction rate securities federman and sherwood federmanlawpublishpathcom represented the plaintiff and troutman sanders represented the company the company defended itself against the suit and in july  the united states district court for the southern district of new york issued a decision dismissing the complaint against all defendants without leave to amend in the order dismissing the lawsuit the court noted that plaintiff had failed to establish a strong inference of scienter and failed to plead facts showing a primary violation of the securities laws suit by mind cti ltd against its accountant kesselmann and kesselmannedit in  mind cti ltd severed its ties with kesselman and kesselmann a pricewaterhousecoopers firm and the companys accountant during the period that the company invested in auction rate securities after  years of working with the accounting firm on or about december  mind cti ltd brought suit against kesselmann and kesselmann alleging breach of contract negligence and breach of fiduciary duty in relation to the companys investment in the auction rate securitiesthe lawsuit seeks compensation equal to the difference between the compensation it received from credit suisse group ag and the approximately us million written off for a total of us  million the cost of defending itself the purported classaction suit filed against it in relation to the auction rate securities matter and the loss of return economic activity and goodwill resulting from kesselmann and kesselmanns actions in totality the claim was  million  million for the investment that was written off  in costs related to claims by investors over  million for loss of interest and yield and  million for loss of business goodwill and waste of administrative resources share buybackedit in september  the companys board of directors authorized a plan for the repurchase of up to  million of the company’s shares in an amount of up to us million as of december   the company had repurchased  million shares at a total purchase price of approximately us million in february  the board of directors authorized additional repurchases of the company’s shares in the total amount of us million pursuant to the  repurchase plan as of december   the company had purchased an aggregate amount of  shares at a total purchase price of us million in november  the board of directors authorized a new plan for the repurchase of the company’s shares in an amount in cash of up to us million as of december   no repurchases had been made under this new plan and it became nonactive in august  the company authorized the reactivation of the  plan allowing for the repurchase of the companys ordinary shares in the open market in an amount in cash of up to  million dividendedit for a technology company mind cti ltd has an unusual dividend policy in that it based on certain approvals by its board of directors and in some special situations the courts of israel pays out ordinary dividends amounting to approximately the companys net income for the previous year once a year a cash dividend will be distributed subject to review and approval by the companys board of directors and the dividend amount will be equal to the companys ebitda plus financial income expenses minus taxes on income from  the company has issued both ordinary dividends under this policy and extraordinary dividends date dividend us                           dividends paid to the companys shareholders in    and  was us million us million us million and us million respectively from  through  the company has paid out approximately  per share to its shareholders on november   the company announced that the  dividend payment would not require court approval since the companys retained earnings would be adequate relative to the dividend in february  the company announced that the  dividend would be  per share productsedit mind cti products include voip and ngn billing convergent operational and business support solutions ossbss g mobile billing solutions mvno and mvne ossbss solutions broadband and cable ossbss solutions wimax billing solutions integrated point of sale solutions for gsm and cdma operators turnkey prepaid solutions customersedit the company’s customers include communication providers as well as new service providers in over  countries across the globe including cellcom eastlink romtelecom moldtelecom china unicom hg italy intelco international telecommunications telefónica del peru singtel sri lanka telecom and verizon historically the companys ossbss business has targeted tier  and tier  wireless wireline isp and cable operators lately however the company has won deals with tier  operators and has won significant mvno and mvne centric deals in israel and in february  the company announced plans to significantly increase the companys employee base in the first half of  to support new projects and the multiple requests of engineering resources it had received from its growing customer base see alsoedit list of israeli companies quoted on the nasdaq list of voip companies silicon wadi startup village yokneam external linksedit mind cti referencesedit  a b form f nasdaq sec filings retrieved    pincas gitit mind cti plans acquisitions globes   retrieved    mind cti reports results for the third quarter   mind to delist from tase marketwire  november   retrieved    form f for fiscal year  retrieved    form f for fiscal year  nasdaq sec filings retrieved    form f for fiscal year  nasdaq sec filings retrieved    form f for fiscal year  nasdaq sec filings retrieved    a b mind cti ltd f filing for fisc